snippet.title: Aashram Chapter 2 - The Dark Side | Official Trailer | Bobby Deol | Prakash Jha | MX Player
snippet.description:
Rakshak ya Bhakshak?
Paavan ya Paapi?
Kya hai Kashipur waale Baba Nirala ka asli roop? 

Hoga khulasa 11-11-2020 ko, #AashramChapter2 mein!

#Aashram #MXOriginalSeries #MXPlayer

Directed by Prakash Jha

Key Cast: Bobby Deol, Aaditi Pohankar, Chandan Roy Sanyal, Darshan Kumaar, Anupria Goenka, Adhyayan Summan, Tridha Choudhury, Vikram Kochhar, Tushar Pandey, Sachin Shroff, Anuritta Jha, Rajeev Siddhartha, Parinitaa Seth, Tanmaay Ranjan, Preeti Sood, Jahangir Khan, Kanupriya Gupta and Navdeep Tomar

About Aashram Chapter 2:
As the true face of Kashipur waale Baba Nirala unfurls, various hidden dark secrets of Aashram are discovered by the Sub-Inspector Ujagar Singh and Constable Sadhu. On the other hand, by roping in a  famous pop-star Tinka Singh, Baba rises as the icon of the youth. With this rising popularity and fame, Baba becomes the center of attraction for both political candidates who are contesting for the upcoming state elections. 

Pammi, who has turned into a blind devotee of Baba, continues to flourish inside the Aashram. How far will her blind faith for Baba sustain? After all, behind his holy image of a messiah, lies the true monster, who exploits young girls. Will Pammi‚Äôs fate be any different from all the other girls who fell victim to this deep nexus?

snippet.description: Rashtriya Janta Dal locates itself in the collective aspirations of people and communities striving to carve out a society based on the premises of social justice and secularism. Since its inception Rashtriya Janta Dal is relentlessly working as the voice of the socially and economically downtrodden sections of the society. The RJD believes in working on and propagating socialist politics and towrds this end the party has been developing solidarity network of landless labourers, peasants and farmers other weaker groups as well as progressive people from other sections of society. Drawing inspiration from Gandhian values as well as following in the great tradition of the socialist leaders, RJD strongly stands against communalism in any form. The party believes that the right of peaceful and democratic dissent including Satyagraha/ non-violent resistance is a fundamental right of the people.

snippet.title: iPhone 12 Pro Durability Test - Is 'Ceramic Shield' Scratchproof?!
snippet.description:
Its time to durability test the new Apple iPhone 12 Pro. Grab your Anker Nano HERE: https://amzn.to/353xHsa (US Offer Code USNANO12) And grab your dbrand glass Screen Protector HERE: https://dbrand.com/iphone-12-glass New iPhones sometimes means new features. Today we find out how durable the new Apple iPhones really are. Apple has changed up the design again. Its still a rectangle. With a screen. But this time around its a blockier rectangle with a screen that might be tougher? We'll have to check to be sure.

Hey everyonee,

Hope you all are doing well. 

It has beeen forever since I did a dance cover, and it was so much fun collab-ing with Vicky and Akku again after sooo many months. Things definitely felt different - like meeting each other after so many months while in masks, and constantly sanitizing, but nothing beats the joy of dancing and working towards something productive. Hope you liked our little effort. Do let me know your thoughts in the comments below üåª

Lots of love
Shirley x

snippet.title: Juventus vs. Barcelona: Extended Highlights | UCL on CBS Sports
snippet.description:
Heading into the match all of the talk was surrounding Juventus and the fact they would be missing their superstar, Cristiano Ronaldo for the second straight UEFA Champions League Group stage match. Barcelona though quickly turned the conversation to just how potent their attack can be surging out to a 1-0 lead in the first 15 minutes.

In the 14‚Äô, Ousmane Demb√©l√© rifled a beautiful, and slightly lucky, shot off of a Juventus defender that found its way to the top left corner of the goal leaving the keeper no chance at making the save. Juventus though fired right back quickly creating a one on one chance with the Barcelona keeper, √Ålvaro Morata did put it home but the goal was called off for being offside which VAR confirmed. Juventus had another real threat this time by Morata in the 30‚Äô, however he timed his run a hair early and when the goal found the back of the net, the flag was up negating the chance. 
To start the second half Juventus picked up right where they left off in the first half. In the 56‚Äô they powered it into the back of the net, but after going to VAR it was ruled a no goal due to offside. 
Barcelona iced the game in stoppage time with a Messi penalty goal to give them the 2-0 win. 

Stream every UEFA Champions League match live on CBS All Access:
http://bit.ly/ucloncbssports

snippet.title: How AMONG US took over the World (with murder).
snippet.description:
Among Us has recently gone from little known indie game - to worldwide phenomenon in just a few months. From 50 concurrent players to 3 million. While we're all enjoying the entertainment side of the game, I wanted to also take a look at the lessons we can draw from the journey of the developers - InnerSloth, a small team of just three people who, not too long ago, were barely getting by trying to keep the game alive. It's a fascinating case study that I think is worth taking a look at.

------------------------------

A natural talent, Quando Rondo was once a small child, secretly singing in the bathroom as a 9-year-old boy in Savannah, GA. His natural gravitation towards music lead to him to hip-hop; he began recording his fledgling verses on his cell phone. He quickly gained traction online, racking up millions of views on YouTube.

Fittingly, he titled his 2018 mixtape 'Life B4 Fame' with the hopes that things would change for the better once his career really took off. He was right‚Äîwithin two days, his mixtape had amassed more than one million streams on MyMixtapez. Things will only go up from there, and if the snippets from his forthcoming Rich Homie Quando project are any sign, he‚Äôs only only getting better with time.

snippet.title: Why Do Things Keep Evolving Into Crabs?
snippet.description:
Help out Eons and take the PBS Digital Studios annual survey: http://to.pbs.org/2020survey

For some reason, animals keep evolving into things that look like crabs, independently, over and over again.¬†What is it about the crab‚Äôs form that makes it so evolutionarily successful that non-crabs are apparently jealous of it?¬†

Thanks to Franz Anthony for all of the ancient crab (and "crab") illustrations featured throughout this episode! http://franzanth.com/ And special thanks to Dr. Jo Wolfe, Dr. Javier Luque, and Dr. Katie Collins for assisting Franz with research for those illustrations. 

And thank you to Dr. Rodney Feldmann for providing a photo of the Paralomis debodeorum fossil!

snippet.title: President Donald Trump: The 60 Minutes 2020 Election Interview
snippet.description:
In an interview that's made headlines this week, Lesley Stahl presses President Trump on once-again rising coronavirus cases and what his priorities would be if re-elected. Stahl also speaks with Mr. Trump's running mate, Vice President Mike Pence. https://cbsn.ws/3mhiSZK

Get new episodes of shows you love across devices the next day, stream local news live, and watch full seasons of CBS fan favorites anytime, anywhere with CBS All Access. Try it free! http://bit.ly/1OQA29B

---
60 Minutes, the most successful American television broadcast in history, began its 52nd season in September. Offering hard-hitting investigative reports, interviews, feature segments and profiles of people in the news, the broadcast began in 1968 is still a hit in 2020. 60 Minutes makes Nielsen‚Äôs weekly Top 10 nearly every week and was the #1 weekly television broadcast three times last season.


The program still averages more than 10 million viewers, more than double the audience of its nearest network news magazine competitor. The average audience for a 60 Minutes broadcast is 150% higher than those of the network morning news programs; the audience dwarfs the number of viewers drawn by the most popular cable news programs.  


About a million more people listen to the 60 Minutes radio simulcast in several major cities and on its companion podcast. Tens of thousands each week experience 60 Minutes online. The broadcast‚Äôs segments can be watched at 60Minutes.com and on the CBS All Access app. Its webcast, 60MinutesOvertime.com, offers content originally produced for the web, including behind-the-scenes video about the production of 60 Minutes stories and timely archival segments.


60 Minutes has won every major broadcast award. Its 25 Peabody and 150 Emmy awards are the most won by any single news program. It has also won 20 duPont-Columbia University journalism awards. Other distinguished journalism honors won multiple times include the George Polk, RTDNA Edward R. Murrow, Investigative Reporters and Editors, RFK Journalism, Sigma Delta Chi and Gerald Loeb awards.

60 Minutes premiered on CBS September 24, 1968. Bill Owens is the program‚Äôs executive producer. The correspondents and contributors of 60 Minutes are Sharyn Alfonsi, Anderson Cooper, John Dickerson, Norah O‚ÄôDonnell, Scott Pelley, Lesley Stahl, Bill Whitaker and L. Jon Wertheim.

snippet.title: Manchester United vs. RB Leipzig: Extended Highlights | UCL on CBS Sports
snippet.description:
Smart Greenwood got the scoring going for Manchester United with a goal in the 21‚Äô. Paul Pogba slipped the ball in to Greenwood in the left channel and the United youngster used one touch and finished low to give Man. U the lead to start the game. 

Manchester United really turned up the pressure in the second half behind Marcus Rashford‚Äôs quick brace. Rashford cut behind the Leipzig back line with a timely run for his first goal in the 74‚Äô then just four minutes later he found the back of the net. The match went from a tightly contested 1-0 game to a big 3-0 Manchester United win in a matter of four minutes.

Man. U would go on to add a goal in the 87‚Äô from Anthony Martial by way of penalty and Marcus Rashford would complete his hat trick in the 90‚Äô+2 to finish the game with a 5-0 dominating win.

Saved by the Bell is streaming November 25th on Peacock. https://www.peacocktv.com/saved-by-the-bell?cid=20201201originalssbtbownsocial262&utm_campaign=20201201originalssbtb&utm_source=yt&utm_medium=own&utm_content=sbtboriginal&utm_term=peacocktv

The highly anticipated reimagining of SAVED BY THE BELL will premiere on Wednesday, Nov. 25 on Peacock. In the new series, when California governor Zack Morris gets into hot water for closing too many underfunded high schools, he proposes they send the affected students to the most well-funded schools in the state ‚Äì including Bayside High. The influx of new students gives the privileged Bayside kids (who never have a problem that can't be solved in twenty-two minutes) a much-needed dose of reality. Elizabeth Berkley Lauren and Mario Lopez star in the new SAVED BY THE BELL series, reprising their roles as Jessie Spano and A.C. Slater. John Michael Higgins also stars as Principal Toddman alongside the new class featuring Belmont Cameli, Dexter Darden, Mitchell Hoog, Alycia Pascual-Pe√±a, Josie Totah and Haskiri Velazquez. Tracey Wigfield serves as writer and executive producer for the series, alongside executive producer Franco Bario. Peter Engel also serves as executive producer. SAVED BY THE BELL is produced by Universal Television, a division of Universal Studio Group.

snippet.title: Geoengineering: A Horrible Idea We Might Have to Do
snippet.description:
To support Kurzgesagt and learn more about Brilliant, go to https://www.brilliant.org/nutshell and sign up for free. The first 200 people that go to that link will get 20% off the annual Premium subscription.
Thanks to our friends from Brilliant for supporting this channel.

Sources & further reading: 
https://sites.google.com/view/sourcesgeoengineering
 
By the end of the 21st century, humanity is becoming desperate. Decades of heatwaves and droughts have led to unusually  poor harvests, while the warming oceans yield fewer fish each year. In the tropical zones, millions suffer from famine and resource wars have made millions more flee to the north. As things quickly get worse, in an act of desperation, the world's governments decide to enact an emergency plan...
It is far from certain that a grim scenario like this will play out. But the failure of world leaders  to effectively address climate change, makes it far from impossible. 
So in the near future it might become necessary to try something radical to slow down rapid climate change: Geoengineering. Interventions so massive in scale that they might undo centuries of human behavior. Or make everything much worse.
What is geoengineering, is it really an option and what if it goes wrong?

localizations.en-GB.title: Geoengineering: A Horrible Idea We Might Have to Do
localizations.en-GB.description:
To support Kurzgesagt and learn more about Brilliant, go to https://www.brilliant.org/nutshell and sign up for free. The first 200 people that go to that link will get 20% off the annual Premium subscription.
Thanks to our friends from Brilliant for supporting this channel.

Sources & further reading: 
https://sites.google.com/view/sourcesgeoengineering
 
By the end of the 21st century, humanity is becoming desperate. Decades of heatwaves and droughts have led to unusually  poor harvests, while the warming oceans yield fewer fish each year. In the tropical zones, millions suffer from famine and resource wars have made millions more flee to the north. As things quickly get worse, in an act of desperation, the world's governments decide to enact an emergency plan...
It is far from certain that a grim scenario like this will play out. But the failure of world leaders  to effectively address climate change, makes it far from impossible. 
So in the near future it might become necessary to try something radical to slow down rapid climate change: Geoengineering. Interventions so massive in scale that they might undo centuries of human behavior. Or make everything much worse.
What is geoengineering, is it really an option and what if it goes wrong?

snippet.title: Joe Biden: The 60 Minutes 2020 Election Interview
snippet.description:
The former vice president talks with Norah O'Donnell about the pandemic, taxes, the Supreme Court, and the "stark" differences between himself and President Trump. O'Donnell also speaks with Mr. Biden's running mate, California Senator Kamala Harris. https://cbsn.ws/3mhiSZK

Subscribe to the 60 Minutes Channel HERE: http://bit.ly/1S7CLRu
Watch Full Episodes of 60 Minutes HERE: http://cbsn.ws/1Qkjo1F
Get more 60 Minutes from 60 Minutes: Overtime HERE: http://cbsn.ws/1KG3sdr
Relive past episodes and interviews with 60 Minutes Rewind HERE: http://cbsn.ws/1PlZiGI
Follow 60 Minutes on Instagram HERE: http://bit.ly/23Xv8Ry
Like 60 Minutes on Facebook HERE: http://on.fb.me/1Xb1Dao
Follow 60 Minutes on Twitter HERE: http://bit.ly/1KxUsqX

Get the latest news and best in original reporting from CBS News delivered to your inbox. Subscribe to newsletters HERE: http://cbsn.ws/1RqHw7T

Get your news on the go! Download CBS News mobile apps HERE: http://cbsn.ws/1Xb1WC8

Get new episodes of shows you love across devices the next day, stream local news live, and watch full seasons of CBS fan favorites anytime, anywhere with CBS All Access. Try it free! http://bit.ly/1OQA29B

---
60 Minutes, the most successful American television broadcast in history, began its 52nd season in September. Offering hard-hitting investigative reports, interviews, feature segments and profiles of people in the news, the broadcast began in 1968 is still a hit in 2020. 60 Minutes makes Nielsen‚Äôs weekly Top 10 nearly every week and was the #1 weekly television broadcast three times last season.


The program still averages more than 10 million viewers, more than double the audience of its nearest network news magazine competitor. The average audience for a 60 Minutes broadcast is 150% higher than those of the network morning news programs; the audience dwarfs the number of viewers drawn by the most popular cable news programs.  


About a million more people listen to the 60 Minutes radio simulcast in several major cities and on its companion podcast. Tens of thousands each week experience 60 Minutes online. The broadcast‚Äôs segments can be watched at 60Minutes.com and on the CBS All Access app. Its webcast, 60MinutesOvertime.com, offers content originally produced for the web, including behind-the-scenes video about the production of 60 Minutes stories and timely archival segments.


60 Minutes has won every major broadcast award. Its 25 Peabody and 150 Emmy awards are the most won by any single news program. It has also won 20 duPont-Columbia University journalism awards. Other distinguished journalism honors won multiple times include the George Polk, RTDNA Edward R. Murrow, Investigative Reporters and Editors, RFK Journalism, Sigma Delta Chi and Gerald Loeb awards.

60 Minutes premiered on CBS September 24, 1968. Bill Owens is the program‚Äôs executive producer. The correspondents and contributors of 60 Minutes are Sharyn Alfonsi, Anderson Cooper, John Dickerson, Norah O‚ÄôDonnell, Scott Pelley, Lesley Stahl, Bill Whitaker and L. Jon Wertheim.

snippet.title: How AMONG US took over the World (with murder).
snippet.description:
Among Us has recently gone from little known indie game - to worldwide phenomenon in just a few months. From 50 concurrent players to 3 million. While we're all enjoying the entertainment side of the game, I wanted to also take a look at the lessons we can draw from the journey of the developers - InnerSloth, a small team of just three people who, not too long ago, were barely getting by trying to keep the game alive. It's a fascinating case study that I think is worth taking a look at.

snippet.description:
Opening in theaters and VOD 25th

Director: Gabriel Range
Starring: Johnny Flynn, Jena Malone, Marc Maron

David Bowie is one of the most seminal legends in music history; but who was the man behind the many faces? In 1971, a 24-year-old fledgling David Bowie (Johnny Flynn) is sent to America to promote his newest record, The Man Who Sold the World. Leaving behind his pregnant wife Angie (Jena Malone), Bowie and his band embark on a makeshift coast-to-coast promotional tour with struggling Mercury Records publicist Rob Oberman (Marc Maron).

snippet.title: Ryan & Shane Get the Drunkest & Read the Most Ghost Stories ‚Ä¢ Too Many Spirits
snippet.description:
Welcome to the SEASON FINALE of our new spooky show- Too Many Spirits! Join us as we read your submitted ghost stories and enjoy cocktails prepared by first-time bartender, Steven Lim. If you've got even spookier stories, leave them in the comments below!

Please drink responsibly, and wear a mask.
This video was filmed under professional supervision. Alcohol intake was monitored, and talent was transported safely. Filming was conducted under recommended COVID-safe guidelines. 

Support us at:
http://www.patreon.com/watcher
http://www.watcherstore.com

The Wicked Watcher 
2 oz. dark rum 
3 oz. ginger beer
1 freshly squeezed lime
Lime slice garnish
2 oz. tequila (leftover from the Boozy Beergarita)

Here we have a play on a Dark n‚Äô Stormy. But because the name of the show is Too Many Spirit, I decided to add one too many spirits, hence the two additional ounces of tequila. This one‚Äôs easy to make - poor the dark rum, ginger beer, lime juice ,tequila, and ice in a glass and stir with a bar spoon. Garnish with that good ol‚Äô lime slice and you have yourself The Wicked Watcher. Cheers!

Created by Katie LeBlanc
Hosts - Ryan Bergara & Shane Madej
Bartender/Cam Op - Steven Lim
Stories by YOU
Editor - Stephen Castro
Production Coordinator/Sound - Brittney Lee
Head of Development - Katie LeBlanc
Creative Director of Post Production - Anthony Frederick
Logo Designed by Casandra Ng

snippet.title: Tamar Braxton Breaks Her Silence Following Suicide Attempt
snippet.description:
Reality TV star and singer Tamar Braxton speaks publicly for the first time after her reported suicide attempt. She details her battle with depression due to her portrayal on reality TV and addresses the allegations of domestic violence with her ex-boyfriend David Adefeso.

snippet.title: Xbox Series X Console Unboxing - A Next Gen Gaming System

Presenting the Tamil trailer of Mookuthi Amman written & directed by RJ Balaji  & NJ Saravanan. The film stars Nayanthara & RJ Balaji in the lead roles. Produced by Dr.Ishari.K.Ganesh under the banner Vels Film International, Mookuthi Amman features Urvashi, Ajay Ghosh, Mouli, Smruthi Venkat in pivotal roles. Girishh Gopalakrishnan has scored the music for the film, which will stream on Disney+ Hotstar VIP from November 14th, 2020.

60 Minutes, the most successful American television broadcast in history, began its 52nd season in September. Offering hard-hitting investigative reports, interviews, feature segments and profiles of people in the news, the broadcast began in 1968 is still a hit in 2020. 60 Minutes makes Nielsen‚Äôs weekly Top 10 nearly every week and was the #1 weekly television broadcast three times last season.


The program still averages more than 10 million viewers, more than double the audience of its nearest network news magazine competitor. The average audience for a 60 Minutes broadcast is 150% higher than those of the network morning news programs; the audience dwarfs the number of viewers drawn by the most popular cable news programs.  


About a million more people listen to the 60 Minutes radio simulcast in several major cities and on its companion podcast. Tens of thousands each week experience 60 Minutes online. The broadcast‚Äôs segments can be watched at 60Minutes.com and on the CBS All Access app. Its webcast, 60MinutesOvertime.com, offers content originally produced for the web, including behind-the-scenes video about the production of 60 Minutes stories and timely archival segments.


60 Minutes has won every major broadcast award. Its 25 Peabody and 150 Emmy awards are the most won by any single news program. It has also won 20 duPont-Columbia University journalism awards. Other distinguished journalism honors won multiple times include the George Polk, RTDNA Edward R. Murrow, Investigative Reporters and Editors, RFK Journalism, Sigma Delta Chi and Gerald Loeb awards.

60 Minutes premiered on CBS September 24, 1968. Bill Owens is the program‚Äôs executive producer. The correspondents and contributors of 60 Minutes are Sharyn Alfonsi, Anderson Cooper, John Dickerson, Norah O‚ÄôDonnell, Scott Pelley, Lesley Stahl, Bill Whitaker and L. Jon Wertheim.

snippet.title: FINALE EPISODE | MICHELLE, NAGISA SA SARILI NIYANG MANTIKA!
snippet.description:
MAHALAGANG PAALALA:

Muli po naming pinapaalala na hanggang ngayon ay SARADO PA RIN PO ANG AMING ACTION CENTER sa TV5 Media Center, Reliance Street, Mandaluyong City.

Hindi pa rin po maaaring pumunta nang personal ang mga complainant para magreklamo kay Idol Raffy dahil sa ating kinahaharap na pandemya at mahigpit pa ring ipinapatupad ang mga safety measures upang maging ligtas ang lahat.

Gayunpaman, puwede ninyong i-PM ang inyong mga sumbong sa OFFICIAL Facebook page ni Idol na RAFFY TULFO IN ACTION na may mahigit 11M followers. Nakahanda pong tumugon sa inyo ang RTIA researchers.

Maraming salamat sa inyong pag-unawa at mag-ingat po tayong lahat!

snippet.title: Ask TSL: Questions Girls Always Wanted To Ask Guys
snippet.description:
In this episode of Ask TSL, we got our MANLIEST MEN to answer questions we got from our females viewers. Let me just tell you, it got HECTIC!

Here are the questions that were answered:
0:00 - Introduction
0:40 - Do men feel intimidated when their girlfriends/ wives earn more than them?
1:43 - If a couple begins to live together, how should duties like household chores and child rearing be split?
2:48 - Are girls who are short and small more attractive?
4:05 - Where do guys go for relationship advice?
6:05 - Are attention-seeking girls irritating, or do guys actually find that cute?
7:03 - Do guys share about their sex lives with their bros?
8:15 - Why is marriage so terrifying for many guys?
9:58 - Why do some men have mostly female friends? Is that a red flag?
11:08 - Does a female‚Äôs attractiveness drop if she wishes to get intimate on the first date?
12:43 - Occasionally, some girls can get bitchy about how other girls look, is it the same for guys?
13:46 - What do you think about periods?
15:43 - What are some things that females have misconceptions of?
16:53 - Guys in Singapore are quite passive and shy when it comes to dating, but are intimidated when a girl asks them out. What‚Äôs going on?!
18:05 - What are your thoughts when girls say that ‚Äòmen are trash‚Äô?
20:26 - Outro & Thoughts

snippet.title: SEVENTEEN (ÏÑ∏Î∏êÌã¥) 'HOME;RUN' Official MV
snippet.description:
SEVENTEEN (ÏÑ∏Î∏êÌã¥) 'HOME;RUN' Official MV

ÏÑ∏Î∏êÌã¥Ïùò Ïù¥Î≤à Ïï®Î≤î ‚Äò; [Semicolon]‚ÄôÏùÄ ÎØ∏Îãà 7Ïßë ‚ÄòÌóπÍ∞ÄÎûò‚ÄôÎ•º ÌÜµÌï¥ Ïù¥ÏïºÍ∏∞Ìïú ‚ÄòÏ≤≠Ï∂ò‚ÄôÏùÑ Ìñ•Ìïú ÏùëÏõêÏùò Î©îÏãúÏßÄÎ•º Îã§ÏãúÍ∏à Í≥µÏú†ÌïòÎ©¥ÏÑú Ìïú Î∞úÏßù Îçî ÎÇòÏïÑÍ∞Ä Ïâº ÏóÜÏù¥ Îã¨Î¶¨Îäî Ï≤≠Ï∂òÏóêÍ≤å ‚ÄòÏû†Íπê Ïâ¨Ïñ¥Í∞ÄÎ©∞ Ï≤≠Ï∂òÏùò Ìñ•Ïó∞ÏùÑ Ï¶êÍ∏∞Ïûê‚ÄôÎùºÎäî ÎçîÏö± ÏÑ±ÏàôÌïú Í∏çÏ†ïÏùò Î©îÏãúÏßÄÎ•º Ï†ÑÌïòÎäî Ïï®Î≤îÏù¥Îã§.

ÌòÑ ÏãúÎåÄÎ•º ÏÇ¥ÏïÑÍ∞ÄÎ©∞ Í≥†Íµ∞Î∂ÑÌà¨ ÌïòÍ≥† ÏûàÎäî Ï≤≠Ï∂òÎì§ÏóêÍ≤å Ïû†ÏãúÎÇòÎßà ‚ÄòÏà® Í≥†Î•º ÏãúÍ∞Ñ‚Äô, ‚ÄòÌï®Íªò ÏõÉÏúºÎ©∞ Ï¶êÍ∏∏ Ïàò ÏûàÎäî ÏãúÍ∞Ñ‚ÄôÏùÑ Î¨∏Ïû•ÏùÑ Ïû†Ïãú ÎÅäÏóàÎã§Í∞Ä Ïù¥Ïñ¥ÏÑú ÏÑ§Î™ÖÏùÑ Í≥ÑÏÜçÌï† Îïå Ïì∞Ïù¥Îäî Î¨∏Ïû• Î∂ÄÌò∏Ïù∏ ‚ÄòSemicolon(ÏÑ∏ÎØ∏ÏΩúÎ°†)‚Äô Ïóê ÎπÑÏú†, ÎèôÏãúÎåÄ Ï≤≠Ï∂òÏúºÎ°ú ÏÇ¥ÏïÑÍ∞ÄÎäî ‚ÄúÏÑ∏Î∏êÌã¥‚Äù Í∑∏Îì§Ïùò Í≥µÍ∞êÏùÑ Ï†ÑÌïòÎäî Î©îÏãúÏßÄÎ•º Ïï®Î≤îÏóê Í∞ÄÎìù Îã¥ÏïÑÎÇ¥Ïñ¥ Ï≤≠Ï∂òÎì§ÏùÑ Ïñ¥Î£®ÎßåÏßà Îî∞ÎúªÌïú ÏúÑÎ°úÏôÄ ÏùëÏõê, Í≥µÍ∞êÏùÑ Ï£ºÎäî Ìù¨ÎßùÏùò Ïô∏Ïπ®ÏùÑ Ï†ÑÌïúÎã§.

ÌÉÄÏù¥ÌãÄÍ≥° ‚ÄòHOME;RUN‚ÄôÏùÄ Ïä§Ïúô Ïû•Î•¥ Í∏∞Î∞òÏùò Î†àÌä∏Î°úÌïú ÏÇ¨Ïö¥ÎìúÍ∞Ä ÎèãÎ≥¥Ïù¥Îäî Í≥°ÏúºÎ°ú Í≤ΩÏæåÌïòÍ≥† ÌÉÄÍ≤©Í∞ê ÎÑòÏπòÎäî ÏÇ¨Ïö¥ÎìúÎ°ú ‚ÄòHOME RUN‚ÄôÏù¥ÎùºÎäî ÌëúÌòÑÏù¥ ÏßÄÎãå ÏßúÎ¶øÌï®ÏùÑ ÌëúÌòÑÌïòÏòÄÍ≥†, Î¨¥ÌïúÌïú ÏÑ±Ïû•ÏùÑ ÏßÄÎãå Ï≤≠Ï∂òÏóêÍ≤å ÌûòÏ∞¨ ÏùëÏõêÍ≥º ÏúÑÎ°úÏùò Î™©ÏÜåÎ¶¨Î•º ÏÑ†ÏÇ¨ÌïúÎã§.

SEVENTEEN‚Äôs new album ‚Äò; [Semicolon]‚Äô is an album where they share the encouraging message for the ‚Äòyouth‚Äô like they did in their 7th mini album ‚ÄòHeng:gar√¶‚Äô and also the positive message that ‚Äòwe should all take a break and enjoy the youth‚Äô with the youth that are running towards their goals without any breaks.

‚ÄòSemicolon,‚Äô which is a punctuation mark used when you pause a sentence and then resume again, is used as a metaphor to portray the ‚Äòtime to take a breath‚Äô and ‚Äòtime to laugh and enjoy together.‚Äô ‚ÄúSEVENTEEN,‚Äù as the youth who are living in the same time period as the other youth who are fighting alone and struggling through their lives, uses this metaphor to convey their hopeful and empathic message through the album to comfort and cheer for the youth.

The title song ‚ÄòHOME;RUN‚Äô is a song based on swing genre where the retro-like sound stands out, and it portrays the excitement that the phrase ‚ÄòHOME RUN‚Äô conveys with cheerful and rhythmical sound. It conveys powerful support and comfort to the youth with limitless potentials.

snippet.title: President Donald Trump: The 60 Minutes 2020 Election Interview
snippet.description:
In an interview that's made headlines this week, Lesley Stahl presses President Trump on once-again rising coronavirus cases and what his priorities would be if re-elected. Stahl also speaks with Mr. Trump's running mate, Vice President Mike Pence. https://cbsn.ws/3mhiSZK

Subscribe to the 60 Minutes Channel HERE: http://bit.ly/1S7CLRu
Watch Full Episodes of 60 Minutes HERE: http://cbsn.ws/1Qkjo1F
Get more 60 Minutes from 60 Minutes: Overtime HERE: http://cbsn.ws/1KG3sdr
Relive past episodes and interviews with 60 Minutes Rewind HERE: http://cbsn.ws/1PlZiGI
Follow 60 Minutes on Instagram HERE: http://bit.ly/23Xv8Ry
Like 60 Minutes on Facebook HERE: http://on.fb.me/1Xb1Dao
Follow 60 Minutes on Twitter HERE: http://bit.ly/1KxUsqX

Get the latest news and best in original reporting from CBS News delivered to your inbox. Subscribe to newsletters HERE: http://cbsn.ws/1RqHw7T

Get your news on the go! Download CBS News mobile apps HERE: http://cbsn.ws/1Xb1WC8

Get new episodes of shows you love across devices the next day, stream local news live, and watch full seasons of CBS fan favorites anytime, anywhere with CBS All Access. Try it free! http://bit.ly/1OQA29B

---
60 Minutes, the most successful American television broadcast in history, began its 52nd season in September. Offering hard-hitting investigative reports, interviews, feature segments and profiles of people in the news, the broadcast began in 1968 is still a hit in 2020. 60 Minutes makes Nielsen‚Äôs weekly Top 10 nearly every week and was the #1 weekly television broadcast three times last season.


The program still averages more than 10 million viewers, more than double the audience of its nearest network news magazine competitor. The average audience for a 60 Minutes broadcast is 150% higher than those of the network morning news programs; the audience dwarfs the number of viewers drawn by the most popular cable news programs.  


About a million more people listen to the 60 Minutes radio simulcast in several major cities and on its companion podcast. Tens of thousands each week experience 60 Minutes online. The broadcast‚Äôs segments can be watched at 60Minutes.com and on the CBS All Access app. Its webcast, 60MinutesOvertime.com, offers content originally produced for the web, including behind-the-scenes video about the production of 60 Minutes stories and timely archival segments.

Kapil Sharma is back with a new 'Salah Center' (Consultancy Business) in a Mohollah with absurd characters. snippet.title: Geoengineering: A Horrible Idea We Might Have to Do
snippet.description:
To support Kurzgesagt and learn more about Brilliant, go to https://www.brilliant.org/nutshell and sign up for free. The first 200 people that go to that link will get 20% off the annual Premium subscription.
Thanks to our friends from Brilliant for supporting this channel.

Sources & further reading: 
https://sites.google.com/view/sourcesgeoengineering
 
By the end of the 21st century, humanity is becoming desperate. Decades of heatwaves and droughts have led to unusually  poor harvests, while the warming oceans yield fewer fish each year. In the tropical zones, millions suffer from famine and resource wars have made millions more flee to the north. As things quickly get worse, in an act of desperation, the world's governments decide to enact an emergency plan...
It is far from certain that a grim scenario like this will play out. But the failure of world leaders  to effectively address climate change, makes it far from impossible. 
So in the near future it might become necessary to try something radical to slow down rapid climate change: Geoengineering. Interventions so massive in scale that they might undo centuries of human behavior. Or make everything much worse.
What is geoengineering, is it really an option and what if it goes wrong?

snippet.title: Among Us But Its A Reality Show 3
snippet.description:
üé¨BEHIND THE SCENES: https://youtu.be/ozufblAjQQw
GET THE MERCH: https://teespring.com/stores/among-us-lol

There are two imposters among us again. After lots of band-aids and medbay visits, our friends are back and better than ever, and as usual are hurling through the dark and unforgiving spacescape with nothing but their tiny brains and a maddening amount of terrible arguments. Our group has to figure out who on the ship are murderers, while making sure they are doing their tasks so that their spaceship doesn't continue its forward frontflipping momentum. Is red sus or is blue? Who should we vote out? Which player is the imposter venting to kill? Will people be murdered by the imposter or by their beloved crewmates? Find out in this week's third episode of Among Us but it's a reality show.

snippet.title: Trump Now Crashing In 2020 As Some Fans Bolt, Echoing Trump U. Debacle | MSNBC
snippet.description:
New 2020 polls from six key states show some Trump 2016 voters abandoning him -- imperiling his narrow coalition. MSNBC's Ari Melber reports on why both the loyalty and enmity among Trump fans is different than for other politicians; and Melber documents how Trump customers turned on his con in the "Trump University" case and explores the parallels to Trump's political standing today. (This interview is from MSNBC‚Äôs ‚ÄúThe Beat with Ari Melber, a news show covering politics, law and culture airing nightly at 6pm ET on MSNBC. http://www.thebeatwithari.com). Aired on 10/19/2020.
¬ª Subscribe to MSNBC: http://on.msnbc.com/SubscribeTomsnbc

About The Beat with Ari Melber: Former lawyer Ari Melber leads this show that provides in-depth analysis of the day's biggest news stories. ""The Beat"" features guest interviews in addition to reporting on stories from across the country. The stories that are covered span across the political spectrum. In addition to his law background, Melber is a former Senate staffer, giving him a unique perspective to share on the political happenings coming out of Washington, D.C.

MSNBC delivers breaking news, in-depth analysis of politics headlines, as well as commentary and informed perspectives. snippet.title: Phrenologie stimmt nie
snippet.description:
‚Ä¶ au√üer rein zuf√§llig :)
Eine k√ºrzlich ver√∂ffentlichte Studie schl√§gt Wellen: mit Hilfe von Machine Learning soll man jemandem am Gesicht ablesen k√∂nnen, wie vertrauensw√ºrdig sie oder er ist. Phrenologie! Lautet der Vorwurf - eine Pseudowissenschaft, nach welcher sich Pers√∂nlichkeiten an der Kopfform ablesen lassen sollen und die in der Geschichte oft zur ‚Äúwissenschaftlichen‚Äù Rechtfertigung von Diskriminierung benutzt wurde. Doch ein genauerer Blick lohnt sich‚Ä¶(f√ºr alle alten Freunde der Sonne - das hier ist Journal Club Deluxe :))

INHALT
0:00 Drama um Studie - Phrenologievorwurf
1:29 Was ist Phrenologie?
8:02 Das Studiendesign / Machine Learning
10:38 Das eigentliche Problem mit dieser Studie
15:05 Keksempfehlungen

maiLab wird produziert von Mai Thi Nguyen-Kim f√ºr funk (ARD & ZDF)
‚ñ∫funk Web-App: https://go.funk.net  
‚ñ∫https://go.funk.net/impressum 


QUELLEN

Die Studie, um die es geht: ein Algorithmus, der historische Gem√§lde nach ihrer wahrgenommenen Vertrauensw√ºrdigkeit zuordnen soll: https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-020-18566-7

Ein Artikel zu der Studie im britischen Boulevardblatt The Sun: https://bit.ly/3mu2a9O 

Gute √úbersichten zu Phrenologie & Franz Joseph Gall: 
https://bit.ly/3jDflmT
https://bit.ly/2TwFKbk 

Zu den verschiedenen Aufgaben der Amygdala (die man normalerweise vor allem als Angstzentrum kennenlernt) geh√∂ren auch: emotionales Lernen und Ged√§chtnis (https://bit.ly/2TLEn9b), Verarbeitung von Belohnung und Strafe (https://go.nature.com/2TC9y6o), Einsch√§tzung der Vertrauensw√ºrdigkeit von Gesichtern (https://bit.ly/37RtlYe). 

F√ºr den Kunstsinn kommt es nicht auf eine einzelne Region an, sondern es ist das Zusammenspiel verschiedener Regionen, das sich bei K√ºnstlern und Nicht-K√ºnstlern unterscheidet: https://go.nature.com/3kQDhF3 

Ein relativ aktueller Artikel, der im Video nicht genannt wird, gibt ebenfalls einen sch√∂nen Einblick: ein ‚ÄúSch√∂nheitszentrum‚Äù in dem Sinn gibt es nicht im Gehirn. Die Sch√∂nheit von Gesichtern und die Sch√∂nheit von Kunst werden in Regionen verarbeitet, die sich nicht √ºberschneiden. https://bit.ly/3mwxrsO 

Ein Teil des Hippocampus ist gr√∂√üer bei Taxifahrern als bei Busfahrern: https://bit.ly/2TwHeSW. Da diese Region auch f√ºr das Ortsged√§chtnis zust√§ndig ist, wird dieser Unterschied als Nachweis daf√ºr gesehen, dass zumindest in manchen F√§llen die Form des Gehirns tats√§chlich mit bestimmten Eigenschaften in Verbindung steht.

Allerdings: eine gro√üe Studie mit MRT-Daten von Tausenden Personen findet keine von der Phrenologie beschriebenen Zusammenh√§nge. Dazu kommt, dass die Form des Kortex generell nur sehr wenig mit der das Sch√§dels zusammenh√§ngt: https://bit.ly/35GkuWt 

Studie zu Machine Learning, bei der festgestellt wurde, dass der Algorithmus menschliche Finger als Identifikationsmerkmal von Schleien benutzt hat (siehe Figure 3, obere Reihe): https://bit.ly/2G6TB5a 

Wie vertrauensw√ºrdig wir ein Gesicht finden h√§ngt auch davon ab, wie attraktiv wir es finden. Dieser Zusammenhang ist sehr stark: je nach Art und Intensit√§t der ausgedr√ºckten Emotion kann diese Korrelation eine St√§rke von bis zu r = 0.90 haben. https://bit.ly/2G8poTt 

Es gibt immer wieder Studien, die berichten, dass man beim Menschen eben doch die Pers√∂nlichkeit am Gesicht ablesen k√∂nnte. Aber es gibt versch. Gr√ºnde f√ºr Zweifel, z.B. dass die Pers√∂nlichkeit des Betrachters eine Rolle spielt (https://bit.ly/3oENFlA) und dass sich Dinge wie Frisur, Kleidung etc. (bei Alltagsfotos) auf die Bewertung niederschlagen (https://go.nature.com/3jz5GOp). Aber auch bei standardisierten Gesichtern gibt es Fallstricke: so wirkt ein maskulineres Gesicht in der Pers√∂nlichkeit dominanter und stabiler, unabh√§ngig davon ob die Person das wirklich ist (https://bit.ly/3mv8Wfj). 
Zu einem gewissen Ma√ü ging in einer Studie aggressives Verhalten bei Eishockeyspielern mit einem breiten Gesicht einher (https://bit.ly/37MSZgA). Die Idee: ein h√∂herer Testosteronlevel f√ºhrt zu einem breiteren Gesicht (https://bit.ly/3oBe3wr) und f√∂rdert auch (in sehr schwachem Ma√ü beim Menschen) aggressives Verhalten (https://bit.ly/31RicT4). Allerdings sind beide Zusammenh√§nge wenig verl√§sslich, da unsere Aggressionslevels im Alltag meist von anderen Dingen abh√§ngen: der Korrelationskoeffizient liegt bei dem sehr geringen Wert von r = 0.08.

snippet.localized.title: Phrenologie stimmt nie
snippet.localized.description:
‚Ä¶ au√üer rein zuf√§llig :)
Eine k√ºrzlich ver√∂ffentlichte Studie schl√§gt Wellen: mit Hilfe von Machine Learning soll man jemandem am Gesicht ablesen k√∂nnen, wie vertrauensw√ºrdig sie oder er ist. Phrenologie! Lautet der Vorwurf - eine Pseudowissenschaft, nach welcher sich Pers√∂nlichkeiten an der Kopfform ablesen lassen sollen und die in der Geschichte oft zur ‚Äúwissenschaftlichen‚Äù Rechtfertigung von Diskriminierung benutzt wurde. Doch ein genauerer Blick lohnt sich‚Ä¶(f√ºr alle alten Freunde der Sonne - das hier ist Journal Club Deluxe :))

0:00 Drama um Studie - Phrenologievorwurf
1:29 Was ist Phrenologie?
8:02 Das Studiendesign / Machine Learning
10:38 Das eigentliche Problem mit dieser Studie
15:05 Keksempfehlungen

maiLab wird produziert von Mai Thi Nguyen-Kim f√ºr funk (ARD & ZDF)
‚ñ∫funk Web-App: https://go.funk.net  
‚ñ∫https://go.funk.net/impressum

Ein Artikel zu der Studie im britischen Boulevardblatt The Sun: https://bit.ly/3mu2a9O 

Gute √úbersichten zu Phrenologie & Franz Joseph Gall:

https://bit.ly/2TwFKbk

Ein relativ aktueller Artikel, der im Video nicht genannt wird, gibt ebenfalls einen sch√∂nen Einblick: ein ‚ÄúSch√∂nheitszentrum‚Äù in dem Sinn gibt es nicht im Gehirn. Die Sch√∂nheit von Gesichtern und die Sch√∂nheit von Kunst werden in Regionen verarbeitet, die sich nicht √ºberschneiden. https://bit.ly/3mwxrsO

snippet.title: Corona-Gipfel: Wie hart werden die Ma√ünahmen? I ZDFheute live
snippet.description:
Kommen neue Kontaktbeschr√§nkungen - und machen Restaurant wieder dicht? Bund und L√§nder beraten √ºber sch√§rfere Corona-Ma√ünahmen.

Wir begleiten die Pressekonferenz von Bundeskanzlerin Angela Merkel und den Ministerpr√§sident*innen live. Mit unserer Hauptstadt-Korrespondentin Nicole Diekmann ordnen wir die Ergebnisse ein. Diskutiert mit und stellt eure Fragen! 



Die Bundesregierung sch√§tzt die Lage ernst ein. Wirtschaftsminister Peter Altmaier (CDU) rechnet schon am Ende dieser Woche mit 20.000 Neuinfektionen am Tag.  Bei den Beratungen von Bund und L√§ndern d√ºrften diese Fragen im Mittelpunkt stehen: Wirken die Ma√ünahmen? W√ºrde ein kurzer, zeitlich beschr√§nkter Shutdown mehr bringen als ein l√§ngerer, der nicht ganz so streng ausf√§llt? W√§re ein sogenannter "Wellenbrecher-Lockdown" verh√§ltnism√§√üig?


----- 
Hier auf ZDFheute Nachrichten erfahrt ihr, was auf der Welt passiert und was uns alle etwas angeht: Wir sorgen f√ºr Durchblick in der Nachrichtenwelt, erkl√§ren die Hintergr√ºnde und gehen auf gesellschaftliche Debatten ein. Diskutiert in Livestreams mit uns und bildet euch eure eigene Meinung mit den Fakten, die wir euch pr√§sentieren.

Abonniert unseren Kanal, um nichts mehr zu verpassen.

Immer auf dem aktuellen Stand seid ihr auf http://www.ZDFheute.de/.
#Merkel #Corona

snippet.title: Skin Picking: Ab wann ist Pickel ausdr√ºcken eine Krankheit? I reporter
snippet.description:
ü§ï Wer an seinen Fingern√§geln knibbelt, im Gesicht selbst kleinste Unreinheiten auf der Haut bearbeitet, Pickel ausquetscht oder aufkratzt, hat m√∂glicherweise nicht nur eine nervige Angewohnheit, sondern eine psychische Krankheit. "Skin Picking Disorder" oder "Dermatillomanie" sind die offiziellen Bezeichnungen f√ºr das, was viele als Knibbelei kennen. Das und Hair Pulling Disorder sind seit 2013 anerkannte psychische Erkrankungen aus dem Spektrum der sich wiederholenden k√∂rperbezogenen Verhaltensweisen.
 
üéµ Musik: 
Miley Cyrus - Midnight Sky
HVOB - Panama

üòû Betroffene besch√§digen ihre Haut oder zupfen Haare aus, bis es blutet, die Wunden vernarben, oder keine Haare mehr wachsen. Ausl√∂ser f√ºr "Knibbelepisoden" k√∂nnen stressigen Situationen sein, aber auch der ganz normale Alltag. Schwierig ist, dass Angeh√∂rige und Freunde oft mit Unverst√§ndnis reagieren und nicht verstehen, dass man dem Drang zu knibbeln einfach nicht widerstehen kann. Das f√ºhrt dazu, dass viele Betroffene z√∂gern, sich Hilfe zu holen. Sie haben Sorge, nicht ernst genommen zu werden oder es ist ihnen nicht bewusst, dass sie m√∂glicherweise eine psychische Erkrankung haben. 
 
ü§í Sarah aus Leipzig hat mittlerweile die Diagnose "Dermatillomanie", allerdings erst nach 10 Jahren Skin Picking und vielen Gespr√§chen mit Therapeutinnen und Therapeuten. Das Wissen, dass es die Krankheiten Dermatillomanie und Trichotillomanie gibt, ist auch unter Therapeutinnen und Therapeuten nicht sehr bekannt, deshalb gibt es nur selten eine Diagnose oder Hilfe.
 
üë©‚Äç‚öïÔ∏è Linda Mehrmann, Psychologin M. Sc. und Doktorandin an der K√∂lner Hochschulambulanz, hat das Online-Selbsttherapie-Programm "Knibbelstopp" mitentwickelt. √úber mehrere Wochen k√∂nnen Betroffene selbstst√§ndig an ihren Symptomen arbeiten, um den Teufelskreis aus Ausl√∂ser - Drang - Knibbeln - Verletzung/abgewertetes Selbstwertgef√ºhl zu durchbrechen.

‚òùÔ∏èOft sind Meinung und Subjektivit√§t alles: Wir aber legen Wert auf Recherche, Transparenz, Unvoreingenommenheit und Relevanz. Wir sind mutig, unideologisch und ergebnisoffen. Meinung machen andere. Wir machen Journalismus. Jeden Mittwoch, 16:30 Uhr gibt es eine neue Folge f√ºr euch. 
 
üë±üèº‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Seit Anfang 2019 ist Maike ein Teil des reporter-Teams und geht dieser neuen Aufgabe mit Leidenschaft nach. Nachdem sie erst Kunstgeschichte und dann Eventmarketing studiert hatte, entschied sie sich dazu, vor der Kamera spannende Geschichten zu erz√§hlen. Ihr findet Maike auf Instagram: @maikejecke

snippet.title: Sind Sportwetten gef√§hrlich? Meini vs. Gl√ºcksspiel || PULS Reportage
snippet.description:
Sportwetten versprechen das schnelle Geld. Am Bundesliga-Samstag mit den Kumpels auf die Lieblingsvereine setzen, gemeinsam mitfiebern und am Ende noch Kohle machen? Ob das Sportwetten-Erlebnis wirklich so abl√§uft, testet Sebastian Meinberg in einem Selbstversuch. Dass Sportwetten aber auch richtig gef√§hrlich werden k√∂nnen, kann Marco best√§tigen. Der 32-J√§hrige rutschte vor drei Jahren in die Sportwettensucht, wurde deshalb straff√§llig und verlor fast alles. F√ºr PULS Reportage hat er Meini seine ganze Geschichte erz√§hlt. Ein Gl√ºcksspiel-Forscher erkl√§rt Sebastian, warum Sportwetten s√ºchtig machen k√∂nnen und warum man ‚Äì ohne Gl√ºck - selbst als Sport-Expert*in Geld verliert. 

Ihr seid euch nicht sicher, ob ihr vielleicht selbst spiels√ºchtig seid, habt Fragen zu Sportwetten oder sucht professionelle Hilfe? Hier findet ihr Infos und Anlaufstellen: https://www.check-dein-spiel.de/ 

Ihr k√∂nnt euch kostenlos und anonym an die Telefonberatung der Bundeszentrale f√ºr gesundheitliche Aufkl√§rung (BZgA) zur Gl√ºcksspielsucht wenden: 0800 1 37 27 00 und auch auf der Seite der Landesstelle Gl√ºcksspielsucht Bayern erfahrt ihr mehr zum Thema Pr√§vention und Selbsthilfe f√ºr Betroffene und Angeh√∂rige: https://www.verspiel-nicht-dein-leben.de/spielsucht/probleme-mit-gluecksspielen  

DAS FETTE BUSINESS MIT SPORTWETTEN 
In den sozialen Netzwerken und rund um sportliche Ereignisse kommt man kaum an ihnen vorbei: Werbungen f√ºr Sportwetten und Online-Gl√ºcksspiele. In den Anzeigen wird damit geworben supereasy und ganz schnell an viel Geld zu kommen, auch mit Bonus-Zahlungen wird gelockt. Doch halten diese Angebote wirklich, was sie versprechen? Angenommen werden sie allemal. Denn laut einer Studie der BZgA haben im Jahr 2017 rund 1,4 Millionen Deutsche auf mindestens ein sportliches Ereignis gewettet. Laut deutschem Sportwettenverband haben deutsche Wettkund*innen im Jahr 2019 sogar rund 9,3 Milliarden an Wetteins√§tzen get√§tigt.  

WIE GEF√ÑHRLICH KANN ONLINE-GL√úCKSSPIEL WERDEN? 
Marco wurde eine Online-Werbung zu Sportwetten zum Verh√§ngnis. Vor drei Jahren wurde er sportwettens√ºchtig, machte immer mehr Schulden, verlor sogar seine Wohnung und wurde straff√§llig. Der 32-J√§hrige sagt: ‚ÄúSportwetten haben mein Leben ruiniert!‚Äù Wie es so weit kommen konnte und wie Marco es da raus geschafft hat, erf√§hrt Sebastian Meinberg in der PULS Reportage. Was den gro√üen Reiz von Online-Sportwetten ausmacht und ob der Erfolg wirklich von sportlichem Fachwissen oder doch nur von Gl√ºck abh√§ngt, kl√§rt Meini mit Tobias Hayer. Er ist Gl√ºcksspiel-Forscher an der Uni Bremen. Und wie ergeht es Sebastian selbst mit Online-Sportwetten? Bei einem Spiel seines Lieblingsvereins probiert er eine Sportwetten-App aus. Was macht das mit ihm und verdient er am Ende wirklich was?  

Wie Online-Sportwettenanbieter mit Deutschrap abkassieren, seht ihr in der PULS Musik Analyse: https://youtu.be/eQHbeK-THs8
